DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: Gavyn and QuinC are standing before a grave in the vemetary

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: So this is the guy, huh?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Maybe this won't make that big of a difference. Maybe this is one of those timelines where the bigger picture ends up the same.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: That's right. The reason we're in this situation. Unfortunately we cannot let his work go unfinished. We must see it through.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I'm afraid even the smallest changes can cause the biggest catastrophies. It's chaos theory, Gavyn.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: So because some 'glitch' that made this guy die when he wasn't supposed to, now we have to pick up the slack and do the things that he was supposed to do?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Precisely!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *sigh* Okay, fine. Let's finish our work here.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Very goo. First and foremost on the agenda: you need to learn how to interact with an object. turn and face the gravestone of this poor chap here and press Q to read what the inscription says.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: The player face the gravestone and reads what it says

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: R.I.P Smith
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Headstone

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Now why don't we have a look around at the environment. Move the camera with the Mouse. You should see a coffin just over there.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You see it? Why not try locking on to it with the Right Mouse Button.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: After Gavyn lock on to the coffin

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: that was easy.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Once locked on to a target, then I'll have the ability to unleash my Quantum Mechanics!! ...Depending on the type of object. Example: look at that rope holding the crate on that scaffolding there. Let's go over and see what we can do with it.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: Gavyn walks up to the rope

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: All right.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Some objects in the environment can be cut, like this rope. We've no use for it. End its miserable existence. Lock on a press the Q button
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Jeez, calm down.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Great! Now the crate's blocking our way out.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Fret naught! I was prepared for this. Objects like that crate can easily be pushed aside. Rinse and repeat, as they say. Lock on and press the Q button.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Is this power even legal?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I'm afraid nothing is legal in the past...Let's find our way back home.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I think I can find the way back from here, but I'm not sure.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's no problem, dear Gavyn. In the cases like this we have the Quest Log. Bring up the pause menu and we'll progress from there.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I guess I know what that means...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: After bringing up the pause menu

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Scroll down and confirm the Quest Log menu.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: From here you can see the list of active quests. Highlight a quest and confirm it to display an active waypoint towards the objective.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: See that graphical change? That means the quest is active. Now exit out of the menu so we can get an idea of our destination.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Whoa, QuinC, why do I have these senses of direction in my head all of a sudden?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Actually, Gavyn, you're just lightheaded from the Hypotension. Common side effect of time travel. Just... walk it off.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I wonder what that's about.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: As do I. Seems to be coming from the State House. Hmmm, let's just move ahead for now. I'm sure we'll discover what the fuss is about later.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Are you Smith?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Man

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: That'd be me.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: This message needs to be delivered to the State House as soon as possible. I'd do it myself but I'm needed elsewhere.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Man

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Uh, sure.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Good. And be careful on your way there. The Redcoats are already here.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Man

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Wait, what?!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Seems to be getting late. We best hurry to the State House quickly.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It'd be best if I stay out of sight.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: What is someone so young doing all alone at this time?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Guard #1

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Uh, oh...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I think it would be in both of our best interests to run at this point... Go!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Get back here! Stop that child! Hey!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Guard #2

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: Gavyn reaches a point blocked by guards

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Seems we're in a bit of a pickle. Quickly, jump into that bundle of hay.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: There's only one way to go, my friend. It's time you learned about Quantum Burst. When you have broken the guard's line of sight, enter a hiding spot to wait for them to lose track of you. to speed up this process, you can activate my special Quantum Burst ability. .But be wary, if you get careless with me, the result will backfire and the guards will be alerted to your immediate location!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: Gavyn makes it back to the cemetery

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I guess they're already here. this is crazy. How're we supposed to get to the State House with all these eyes?!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's still imperative this letter is delivered. I'm sure the contact will be handing it off to the necessary sources to relieve Philadelphia of this... congestion. Now, you remember all those things you learned earlier today? Time to put it into action. We can see our destination from here, so let's try to find a way over the north end of the cemetary.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okay... let's see what looks suspiciously moveable around here...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavin

DialogueEditorDialogueObject.name: After Gavyn makes it over the cemetary wall

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Oh, man we're so close, too. How're we gonna get past all of them?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I didn't want you to do this unless circumstances demanded it, but I believe I have a solution. Gavyn, if you sneak behind a guard without your presence being known, you can lock-on and press the Q button to have me give them a good taze. That ought to knock them out long enough for you to move ofrward. Combine this ability with Quantum burst and we shouldn't have too great a problem.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Very good, Gavyn. We'll make a spy out of you yet.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I'm just tryna taze some more people.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavin

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Ohohoho. There'll be plenty of tazing ahead of us.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okay, well, how are we going to get in the building? We obviously can't use the front door.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Come, dear child, start using that head of yours and observe your environment. We can still get into the building. Think creatively.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I'm starting to impress myself with my own craftiness.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gavyn

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You can pat yourself on the back later. We've still to deliver the letter. Remember: our contact should be at the entrance to the bell tower.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: QuinC
